      "message": "[warning] Line 116: The parser accepts any positive unsigned value, but the result is narrowed to `int` before being passed to `VideoMixer`. Values greater than `INT_MAX` can wrap or become implementation-defined negative dimensions, so a malformed config can still reach the mixer as invalid sizes. Validate the bounds before casting and fall back to auto when out of range.\n\n```suggestion\n    if (res.size() \u003d\u003d 2u and res[0] \u003e 0 and res[1] \u003e 0\n        and res[0] \u003c\u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(std::numeric_limits\u003cint\u003e::max())\n        and res[1] \u003c\u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(std::numeric_limits\u003cint\u003e::max())) {\n        conf_res \u003d {static_cast\u003cint\u003e(res[0]), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(res[1])};\n```\n\nThis also requires including `\u003climits\u003e`.",
